{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"So yeah, I'm a newspaper cartoonist --"},{"time":3000,"text":"political cartoonist."},{"time":5000,"text":"I don't know if you've heard about it -- newspapers?"},{"time":8000,"text":"It's a sort of paper-based reader."},{"time":11000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":14000,"text":"It's lighter than an iPad,"},{"time":16000,"text":"it's a bit cheaper."},{"time":19000,"text":"You know what they say?"},{"time":21000,"text":"They say the print media is dying --"},{"time":24000,"text":"who says that? Well, the media."},{"time":27000,"text":"But this is no news, right?"},{"time":30000,"text":"You've read about it already."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"Ladies and gentlemen,"},{"time":40000,"text":"the world has gotten smaller."},{"time":42000,"text":"I know it's a cliche, but look,"},{"time":45000,"text":"look how small,"},{"time":48000,"text":"how tiny it has gotten."},{"time":50000,"text":"And you know the reason why, of course."},{"time":52000,"text":"This is because of technology -- yeah."},{"time":55000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":58000,"text":"Any computer designers in the room?"},{"time":62000,"text":"Yeah well,"},{"time":64000,"text":"you guys are making my life miserable"},{"time":67000,"text":"because track pads used to be round,"},{"time":69000,"text":"a nice round shape."},{"time":71000,"text":"That makes a good cartoon."},{"time":73000,"text":"But what are you going to do with a flat track pad,"},{"time":75000,"text":"those square things?"},{"time":77000,"text":"There's nothing I can do as a cartoonist."},{"time":79000,"text":"Well, I know the world is flat now."},{"time":82000,"text":"That's true."},{"time":83000,"text":"And the Internet has reached"},{"time":85000,"text":"every corner of the world,"},{"time":87000,"text":"the poorest, the remotest places."},{"time":89000,"text":"Every village in Africa now has a cyber cafe."},{"time":94000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":100000,"text":"Don't go asking for a Frappuccino there."},{"time":104000,"text":"So we are bridging the digital divide."},{"time":107000,"text":"The Third World is connected,"},{"time":109000,"text":"we are connected."},{"time":111000,"text":"And what happens next?"},{"time":113000,"text":"Well, you've got mail."},{"time":118000,"text":"Yeah."},{"time":120000,"text":"Well, the Internet has empowered us."},{"time":123000,"text":"It has empowered you,"},{"time":125000,"text":"it has empowered me"},{"time":127000,"text":"and it has empowered some other guys as well."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":136000,"text":"You know, these last two cartoons --"},{"time":138000,"text":"I did them live"},{"time":140000,"text":"during a conference in Hanoi."},{"time":142000,"text":"And they were not used to that"},{"time":145000,"text":"in communist 2.0 Vietnam."},{"time":148000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":150000,"text":"So I was cartooning live on a wide screen --"},{"time":153000,"text":"it was quite a sensation --"},{"time":155000,"text":"and then this guy came to me."},{"time":157000,"text":"He was taking pictures of me and of my sketches,"},{"time":159000,"text":"and I thought, \"This is great, a Vietnamese fan.\""},{"time":163000,"text":"And as he came the second day,"},{"time":165000,"text":"I thought, \"Wow, that's really a cartoon lover.\""},{"time":168000,"text":"And on the third day, I finally understood,"},{"time":170000,"text":"the guy was actually on duty."},{"time":174000,"text":"So by now, there must be a hundred pictures of me"},{"time":176000,"text":"smiling with my sketches"},{"time":178000,"text":"in the files of the Vietnamese police."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":183000,"text":"No, but it's true: the Internet has changed the world."},{"time":186000,"text":"It has rocked the music industry;"},{"time":188000,"text":"it has changed the way we consume music."},{"time":190000,"text":"For those of you old enough to remember,"},{"time":192000,"text":"we used to have to go to the store"},{"time":194000,"text":"to steal it."},{"time":196000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":200000,"text":"And it has changed the way"},{"time":202000,"text":"your future employer"},{"time":204000,"text":"will look at your application."},{"time":206000,"text":"So be careful"},{"time":208000,"text":"with that Facebook account --"},{"time":211000,"text":"your momma told you, be careful."},{"time":215000,"text":"And technology has set us free --"},{"time":219000,"text":"this is free WiFi."},{"time":221000,"text":"But yeah, it has liberated us"},{"time":223000,"text":"from the office desk."},{"time":226000,"text":"This is your life,"},{"time":229000,"text":"enjoy it."},{"time":231000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":234000,"text":"In short, technology, the internet,"},{"time":237000,"text":"they have changed our lifestyle."},{"time":240000,"text":"Tech guru, like this man --"},{"time":242000,"text":"that a German magazine called the philosopher of the 21st century --"},{"time":245000,"text":"they are shaping the way we do things."},{"time":247000,"text":"They are shaping the way we consume."},{"time":249000,"text":"They are shaping our very desires."},{"time":252000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":256000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":263000,"text":"You will not like it."},{"time":267000,"text":"And technology has even changed"},{"time":269000,"text":"our relationship to God."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"Now I shouldn't get into this."},{"time":280000,"text":"Religion and political cartoons,"},{"time":282000,"text":"as you may have heard,"},{"time":284000,"text":"make a difficult couple,"},{"time":286000,"text":"ever since that day of 2005,"},{"time":288000,"text":"when a bunch of cartoonists in Denmark"},{"time":290000,"text":"drew cartoons that had repercussions all over the world --"},{"time":293000,"text":"demonstrations, fatwa,"},{"time":295000,"text":"they provoked violence. People died in the violence."},{"time":298000,"text":"This was so sickening;"},{"time":300000,"text":"people died because of cartoons."},{"time":304000,"text":"I mean --"},{"time":308000,"text":"I had the feeling at the time"},{"time":310000,"text":"that cartoons had been used by both sides, actually."},{"time":313000,"text":"They were used first by a Danish newspaper,"},{"time":315000,"text":"which wanted to make a point on Islam."},{"time":317000,"text":"A Danish cartoonist told me he was one of the 24"},{"time":320000,"text":"who received the assignment to draw the prophet --"},{"time":322000,"text":"12 of them refused. Did you know that?"},{"time":325000,"text":"He told me, \"Nobody has to tell me what I should draw."},{"time":328000,"text":"This is not how it works.\""},{"time":330000,"text":"And then, of course, they were used"},{"time":332000,"text":"by extremists and politicians on the other side."},{"time":335000,"text":"They wanted to stir up controversy."},{"time":337000,"text":"You know the story."},{"time":340000,"text":"We know that cartoons can be used as weapons."},{"time":343000,"text":"History tells us,"},{"time":345000,"text":"they've been used by the Nazis"},{"time":347000,"text":"to attack the Jews."},{"time":349000,"text":"And here we are now."},{"time":351000,"text":"In the United Nations,"},{"time":353000,"text":"half of the world is pushing"},{"time":356000,"text":"to penalize the offense to religion --"},{"time":358000,"text":"they call it the defamation of religion --"},{"time":360000,"text":"while the other half of the world is fighting back"},{"time":362000,"text":"in defense of freedom of speech."},{"time":365000,"text":"So the clash of civilizations is here,"},{"time":367000,"text":"and cartoons are at the middle of it?"},{"time":371000,"text":"This got me thinking."},{"time":374000,"text":"Now you see me thinking"},{"time":376000,"text":"at my kitchen table,"},{"time":378000,"text":"and since you're in my kitchen,"},{"time":380000,"text":"please meet my wife."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":388000,"text":"In 2006, a few months after,"},{"time":391000,"text":"I went Ivory Coast --"},{"time":393000,"text":"Western Africa."},{"time":395000,"text":"Now, talk of a divided place -- the country was cut in two."},{"time":398000,"text":"You had a rebellion in the North,"},{"time":400000,"text":"the government in the South -- the capital, Abidjan --"},{"time":402000,"text":"and in the middle, the French army."},{"time":405000,"text":"This looks like a giant hamburger."},{"time":407000,"text":"You don't want to be the ham in the middle."},{"time":412000,"text":"I was there to report on that story"},{"time":414000,"text":"in cartoons."},{"time":416000,"text":"I've been doing this for the last 15 years;"},{"time":419000,"text":"it's my side job, if you want."},{"time":421000,"text":"So you see the style is different."},{"time":423000,"text":"This is more serious than maybe editorial cartooning."},{"time":426000,"text":"I went to places like Gaza"},{"time":429000,"text":"during the war in 2009."},{"time":432000,"text":"So this is really journalism in cartoons."},{"time":434000,"text":"You'll hear more and more about it."},{"time":436000,"text":"This is the future of journalism, I think."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"And of course, I went to see the rebels in the north."},{"time":443000,"text":"Those were poor guys fighting for their rights."},{"time":445000,"text":"There was an ethnic side to this conflict"},{"time":447000,"text":"as very often in Africa."},{"time":450000,"text":"And I went to see the Dozo."},{"time":452000,"text":"The Dozo, they are the traditional hunters"},{"time":454000,"text":"of West Africa."},{"time":456000,"text":"People fear them --"},{"time":458000,"text":"they help the rebellion a lot."},{"time":460000,"text":"They are believed to have magical powers."},{"time":462000,"text":"They can disappear and escape bullets."},{"time":466000,"text":"I went to see a Dozo chief;"},{"time":468000,"text":"he told me about his magical powers."},{"time":471000,"text":"He said, \"I can chop your head off right away"},{"time":474000,"text":"and bring you back to life.\""},{"time":477000,"text":"I said, \"Well, maybe we don't have time for this right now.\""},{"time":480000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":482000,"text":"\"Another time.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":484000,"text":"So back in Abidjan,"},{"time":487000,"text":"I was given a chance to lead a workshop"},{"time":489000,"text":"with local cartoonists there"},{"time":491000,"text":"and I thought, yes,"},{"time":493000,"text":"in a context like this, cartoons can really be used as weapons"},{"time":496000,"text":"against the other side."},{"time":498000,"text":"I mean, the press in Ivory Coast was bitterly divided --"},{"time":502000,"text":"it was compared to the media in Rwanda"},{"time":504000,"text":"before the genocide --"},{"time":506000,"text":"so imagine."},{"time":508000,"text":"And what can a cartoonist do?"},{"time":510000,"text":"Sometimes editors would tell their cartoonists"},{"time":512000,"text":"to draw what they wanted to see,"},{"time":514000,"text":"and the guy has to feed his family, right?"},{"time":518000,"text":"So the idea was pretty simple."},{"time":520000,"text":"We brought together cartoonists"},{"time":523000,"text":"from all sides in Ivory Coast."},{"time":526000,"text":"We took them away from their newspaper for three days."},{"time":529000,"text":"And I asked them to do a project together,"},{"time":532000,"text":"tackle the issues affecting their country"},{"time":535000,"text":"in cartoons, yes, in cartoons."},{"time":538000,"text":"Show the positive power of cartoons."},{"time":540000,"text":"It's a great tool of communication"},{"time":542000,"text":"for bad or for good."},{"time":544000,"text":"And cartoons can cross boundaries,"},{"time":546000,"text":"as you have seen."},{"time":548000,"text":"And humor is a good way, I think,"},{"time":550000,"text":"to address serious issues."},{"time":553000,"text":"And I'm very proud of what they did."},{"time":555000,"text":"I mean, they didn't agree with each other -- that was not the point."},{"time":558000,"text":"And I didn't ask them to do nice cartoons."},{"time":560000,"text":"The first day, they were even shouting at each other."},{"time":562000,"text":"But they came up with a book,"},{"time":564000,"text":"looking back at 13 years"},{"time":567000,"text":"of political crisis in Ivory Coast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"So the idea was there."},{"time":572000,"text":"And I've been doing projects like this,"},{"time":574000,"text":"in 2009 in Lebanon,"},{"time":576000,"text":"this year in Kenya, back in January."},{"time":579000,"text":"In Lebanon, it was not a book."},{"time":581000,"text":"The idea was to have --"},{"time":583000,"text":"the same principal, a divided country --"},{"time":585000,"text":"take cartoonists from all sides"},{"time":587000,"text":"and let them do something together."},{"time":589000,"text":"So in Lebanon,"},{"time":591000,"text":"we enrolled the newspaper editors,"},{"time":593000,"text":"and we got them to publish"},{"time":595000,"text":"eight cartoonists from all sides all together on the same page,"},{"time":598000,"text":"addressing the issue affecting Lebanon,"},{"time":601000,"text":"like religion in politics and everyday life."},{"time":604000,"text":"And it worked."},{"time":606000,"text":"For three days, almost all the newspapers of Beirut"},{"time":609000,"text":"published all those cartoonists together --"},{"time":611000,"text":"anti-government,"},{"time":613000,"text":"pro-government,"},{"time":615000,"text":"Christian,"},{"time":618000,"text":"Muslim, of course,"},{"time":620000,"text":"English-speaking, well, you name it."},{"time":622000,"text":"So this was a great project."},{"time":624000,"text":"And then in Kenya, what we did"},{"time":627000,"text":"was addressing the issue of ethnicity,"},{"time":629000,"text":"which is a poison in a lot of places in Africa."},{"time":632000,"text":"And we did video clips --"},{"time":635000,"text":"you can see them if you go to YouTube/Kenyatoons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":642000,"text":"So, preaching for freedom of speech"},{"time":644000,"text":"is easy here,"},{"time":646000,"text":"but as you have seen"},{"time":648000,"text":"in contexts of repression or division,"},{"time":651000,"text":"again, what can a cartoonist do?"},{"time":653000,"text":"He has to keep his job."},{"time":657000,"text":"Well I believe that in any context anywhere,"},{"time":660000,"text":"he always has the choice at least"},{"time":662000,"text":"not to do a cartoon"},{"time":664000,"text":"that will feed hatred."},{"time":667000,"text":"And that's the message I try to convey to them."},{"time":670000,"text":"I think we all always have the choice in the end"},{"time":673000,"text":"not to do the bad thing."},{"time":677000,"text":"But we need to support"},{"time":679000,"text":"these [unclear], critical"},{"time":681000,"text":"and responsible voices"},{"time":684000,"text":"in Africa, in Lebanon,"},{"time":686000,"text":"in your local newspaper,"},{"time":689000,"text":"in the Apple store."},{"time":693000,"text":"Today, tech companies"},{"time":695000,"text":"are the world's largest editors."},{"time":698000,"text":"They decide what is too offensive"},{"time":700000,"text":"or too provocative for you to see."},{"time":702000,"text":"So really, it's not about the freedom of cartoonists;"},{"time":705000,"text":"it's about your freedoms."},{"time":708000,"text":"And for dictators all over the world,"},{"time":714000,"text":"the good news"},{"time":716000,"text":"is when cartoonists,"},{"time":718000,"text":"journalists and activists shut up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":725000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}